race.comment: TIPSY GYPSY (11) settled near the tail of a small field then went through her gears in good style to get up for third on debut over 1000m at this track ten days ago. Perfectly placed out to this trip and the quick turnaround is a positive sign from the stable. Looks the one to beat with the help of an inside gate. SHOT OF SATIN (7) went hard early but was feeble in the closing stages first-up over this course and distance recently. Might be a surprise packet with the blinkers going on today. TUXEDO MISS (12) wound up late but was never a threat last start over this distance at Kyneton. That was her first run in over a month so there is scope for improvement. Market watch on THINK BABY (10) first-up from an eight-week let-up for the new stable. Headwater first starter WETLAND (14) has shown enough in recent jump-outs to suggest she is ready to run well.
